	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have compared the power connectors on the NTSC and PAL NES. The difference is that the PAL one is more picky, as the inner pin is wider. This means that a PAL power adaptor will fit the NTSC as well, but not vice-versa, since the NTSC adaptor is the one that has a narrower plug and will only fit the NTSC NES. So you don't need a new adaptor if you have one for your PAL NES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


